      },
      "date": "2013-12-19 17:05:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nPatch Set 5:\n\n> Actually we must take the open lock even if there is no layout. This is because the open lock taking will flush the existing conflicting open locks held by other clients. If we don't do that, then the clients will continue to hold the locks and cached filehandles that might prevent us from opening a file for write or for exec. See bugzilla bug 2443 for more details.\n\nIndeed. I was confused partially because this is still a bit broken. There are paths through mdt_object_open_lock() that really occur and don't flush open locks. I'll create an issue.",
